<h1>
D I A S P O R A *
</h1>
<h2>
The community-run, distributed social network
</h2>
<h4>
JoinDiaspora.com is one of <a href="http://podupti.me">many installations</a> of
<a href="http://github.com/diaspora/diaspora">diaspora*</a>
</h4>
</div>
</div>
<div class='container' id='page'>
<div class='row' id='steps'>
<div class='span6'>
<h2>Decentralization</h2>
<p>Diaspora* is completely decentralized, and any person from any pod can communicate with one
another! You can register at any of these <a href="http://podupti.me">other pods</a> as well. You can also choose to
<a href="https://wiki.diasporafoundation.org/FAQ_for_pod_maintainers">set up your own pod</a> if you'd like.</p>
</div>
<div class='span6'>
<h1>Tor .onion Service</h1>
<p>
Tor makes it possible for users to hide their locations
while offering various kinds of services,
such as web publishing or an instant messaging server:
</p>
<code>diasporaaqmjixh5.onion</code>
</div>
</div>
<div class='row' id='steps'>
<div class='span6'>
<h2>Make a contribution!</h2>
<p>
Make Diaspora even better! Fork the project on
<a href="http://github.com/diaspora/diaspora">Github</a>
make some changes, and submit a pull request.
</p>
</div>
<div class='span6'>
<h2>
Diaspora* goes Non-Profit
</h2>
<p>
Help support our mission of decentralizing the social web!
</p>
<a href="https://blog.diasporafoundation.org/1-diaspora-celebrates-one-year-as-a-community-project">Learn more</a>
</div>
</div>
